The paper deals with the query complexity of Boolean functions, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The use of Grover's algorithm and quantum speedups suggests that the paper may belong to cs.QI (Quantum Physics), while the focus on randomized and quantum query complexities suggests that it may belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The construction of a total Boolean function also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these sub-categories often deal with Boolean functions and their properties.
